# Credentials for a signed + notarized release build (src-tauri/scripts/build-release.sh).
# Copy to src-tauri/.env.release (gitignored) and fill in. Never commit the real file.
#
# APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY — exact name from `security find-identity -p codesigning -v`.
# APPLE_ID              — your Apple account email.
# APPLE_PASSWORD        — an app-specific password from https://appleid.apple.com (NOT
#                         your account password); revoke + regenerate any time.
# APPLE_TEAM_ID         — 10-character team id (in the identity name's parentheses).
#
# Auto-updater signing (optional — separate from Apple signing). Set these to
# emit the signed updater artifacts the in-app updater downloads. Generate once
# with `pnpm tauri signer generate -w ~/.tauri/compose.key`, paste the PUBLIC key
# into tauri.conf.json `plugins.updater.pubkey`, and keep the private key secret.
# TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY          — the private key file's contents (or its path).
# TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD — the password set at generation ("" if none).

APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Your Name (XXXXXXXXXX)"
APPLE_ID="you@example.com"
APPLE_PASSWORD="xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx"
APPLE_TEAM_ID="XXXXXXXXXX"

# TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY="$(cat ~/.tauri/compose.key)"
# TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD=""
